Let $P$ be the point $P_{i,j}$ on $\overline{AB}$ such that $AP_{i,j} = i$ and $BP_{i,j} = 2 - i,$ and let $Q$ be the point $Q_{j,k}$ on $\overline{BC}$ such that $BQ_{j,k} = j$ and $CQ_{j,k} = 2 - j.$  Then let $R$ be the point $R_{k,i}$ on $\overline{CD}$ such that $CR_{k,i} = k$ and $DR_{k,i} = 2 - k.$

Let $G$ be the centroid of $\triangle PQR.$  Then
\[\overrightarrow{G} = \frac{\overrightarrow{P} + \overrightarrow{Q} + \overrightarrow{R}}{3}.\]We can write $\overrightarrow{P}$ as
\[\overrightarrow{P} = (i,0) + j \left( \frac{1}{5} \overrightarrow{AB} \right),\]and $\overrightarrow{Q}$ as
\[\overrightarrow{Q} = (2, j) + k \left( \frac{1}{5} \overrightarrow{BC} \right).\]Also, $\overrightarrow{R}$ is
\[\overrightarrow{R} = (2 - k, 2) + i \left( \frac{1}{5} \overrightarrow{CD} \right).\]Then
